&lt;p&gt;I completely recreated the rider (or stand-alone character) for the Tale sprite graphic.  The major goal was to represent both genders equally in the game.  On the way, I created several hair styles and facial expressions, articulated the arms into three positions for each gender, and created a lot of layers.  Here's the breakdown:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;male or female&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;round, oval, or angular head&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;arms out stretched, bent for holding shields and such, or hanging at your sides&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;shirt with detachable sleeves&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;pants or shorts&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;shoes, boots, or sandals&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;buckler, roman shield, hero shield&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;long or short, lobed or round ears&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;11 hair styles&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;14 facial expressions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
